same graphic as leather

From: "Webber, Jessica" <webber@...>
To: <eqbards@egroups.com>
Sent: Wednesday, July 12, 2000 3:11 PM
Subject: RE: [eqbards] Fashion Police


> > From: Jennifer McComb [mailto:mccomb@...]
>
> > I have mostly banded, plus bronze pants, gauntlets, and helm. The
> > Dwarven tunic blends well enough with the tunic. But, I really hate
> > the look of the bronze helm on wood elf females. It totally covers my
> > face. The banded has a nice egyptian look, but the bronze looks like
> > I'm wearing a small trash can on my head. I may just give up the
> > extra AC and get a banded helm instead.
>
> It was really the dwarven tunic/bronze sleeves that I couldn't take (wood
> elf also). The pants could use to be replaced also. I've just got to
find
> someone selling banded.
>
> I lucked out with the hat. The guildmate donating the bronze hated bronze
> helms on wood elves soooo much she gave me a lumberjacks cap. I'm not
sure
> what it looks like other than it doesn't quite show from the front (like
the
> patchwork it replaced). Nice stats though.
>
> Peace
> Evulia, twink of twelve tunes, Tunare
